Made the most delicious tiramisu cupcakes, even a few minis for Marty 👼🏾

What you’ll need:
4 tbsp softened butter
3 oz mascarpone
1 large egg
½ cup granulated sugar
¼ cup neutral oil
5 oz flour
¼ oz baking powder
⅔ cup water
5 oz powdered sugar
¼ oz espresso powder
¼ oz unsweetened cocoa powder
1 tsp vanilla extract
1 tsp coarse salt

Preheat // oven to 350°F. Remove butter & mascarpone from fridge, set aside to soften at room temperature. Line cupcake tin with paper liners or coat with butter.

Make batter // in a medium size bowl, whisk to combine egg, granulated sugar & oil. Add flour, baking powder, water, vanilla & salt. Whisk until smooth. Pour batter into prepared cupcake tin & fill to the top.

Bake // on center oven rack until cupcakes look set & a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, 18–22 min. Let cupcakes cool completely in cupcake tin.

Prep espresso // in a small bowl (wide enough to dip cupcakes into), whisk espresso powder with ⅓ cup hot tap water until dissolved. Pierce top of cupcakes a few times with a fork or toothpick. Dip cupcake tops into espresso for a few seconds, lift & let excess drip back into bowl.

Frosting // transfer softened butter & mascarpone to medium size bowl. Use an electric mixer to beat until cream (1–2 min). Add powdered sugar & pinch of salt. Beat on lowest speed until sugar is fully combined then increase speed & beat until frosting is light & fluffy (2–3 min).

Spread // frosting over tops of cupcakes. Use a fine mesh sieve to sift cocoa powder over the top of frosted cupcakes.

Enjoy! ✨☕️🧁🍫✨

Anybody else so fucking sick it’s not even funny? 🤧😵‍💫🥱😤😷🤒😪🫠 I was sick for 12 days straight with almost every symptom in the book all at once: sore throat, white tonsils, swollen lymph nodes, back-to-back sneezing, pronounced sinusitis, congestion, runny nose in the daytime, stuffy nose at night, phlegm in the mornings, continuous plugged ears, obvious inflammation, noticeable respiratory wheezing, migraines, sleepless fatigue and the most persistent dry cough / post-nasal drip from hell. Then I got hit with norovirus or gastroenteritis for 24 hours the day after coming home from Vegas. I was well and fine for 5 days, but now that first sickness is back with a vengeance and worse than before. Urgent care has tested for strep, tonsillitis, influenza a & b, pneumonia, bronchitis and covid… all results negative. Any suggestions for alleviation would be extra appreciated, though it feels like I’ve exhausted my list of remedies and treatments. Currently on a (mostly) liquid diet. Please share any tips or tricks I may have missed!! 😮‍💨🍜

*edit // may be symptoms of EBV flare up after being diagnosed in September. Thank you to those of you who brought this to my attention.

Admittedly I bought this book solely for the cover, but it turned out to be deeply disturbing in the best, most brutal and bleakest ways. Another uniquely fictitious dystopian story that’s eerily easy to envision, and in the end reminds us that humans are animals. Simply put, an inexplicable virus has eradicated animals which has left humanity to turn to cannibalism in order to satiate our ceaseless hunger for flesh and blood. @agustinabazterrica’s writing was astounding, my jaw dropped repeatedly as I devoured every single page. I have a feeling I’ll be thinking about this one for a long time and will never listen to Summertime the same. 🐮🤰🏼🌼🫖🌳🪽☀️🎶 4.5/5

Get the Moroccan Salmon Skewer served over North African spiced tomato curry alongside labneh & pita! The Fried Cauliflower with berbere is delish! Radicchio Salad with mint & sumac vinaigrette, yes please! Excellent Chermoula as a side sauce! Vanilla Citrus Gazoz (Turkish sparkle lemonade) to drink! Finish with the Date & Cardamom Ice Cream! Next time I’m definitely trying the Filo + Feta!

The Hood River Railbikes were so much fun! What a great date idea or thing to do if you have visitors in town. My mom & I love doing stuff like this & we had the best time! 🚂🛤️🌋🌳🍎🍇🍷🏞️

Perfect gloomy morning to try @clevrblends new London Fog & eat mango sticky rice for breakfast. If you like luxurious Italian bergamot oil, organic Indonesian vanilla & high altitude Assam black tea, you’ll love this! It’s creamy dreamy when I steamed it with oat milk. I truly love this woman-owned brand for not only including adaptogens (mushrooms, ashwagandha) + 500 million probiotics, but being tasty in very cute packaging! I checked & my code still works, use AINSLEY15 for 15% off your order. ☁️🍄💖☺️🫖☁️
